  "narrative": "DRIVER\nUSD leads D1 CSM at 100 but H4 CSM has collapsed to 44, a 56-point divergence flagged as the single most important short-term signal in this brief, while CHF H4 CSM surges to 100 versus D1 at 33 and AUD H4 CSM hits 70 versus D1 at 31, signaling an intraday regime rotation away from USD and into CHF and AUD. USDCHF is the sharpest expression with H4 sell signal and EURUSD negative 0.89 correlation confirming CHF bid across the board, while AUDUSD and AUDJPY printing correlated strength at 0.90 extends the AUD move with NZD amplifying via NZDUSD and NZDJPY cluster. USDCAD D1 and H4 both strong buy at plus 5 score remains the one USD long that holds alignment and overrides the broader USD fade narrative.\n\nMOMENTUM\nGaining: None\nFading: None\n\nWATCH\nUSDCAD reaction to any WTI oil extension above 96.6 invalidates the strong buy setup and flips CAD bid\nCHF H4 acceleration confirmation on next USDCHF H4 close determines whether EURUSD breaks below current D1 sell trigger\nCopper holding above 6.34 sustains AUDUSD H4 buy pressure and targets extension through AUDJPY correlated at 0.90",
